<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="272" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/185a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-10T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 10, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>836. Over 3 weeks ago War Trade Board requested of Dutch commission here
                            that all steamers be released for West Indian and South American round
                            trips at rate of 35 shillings. No reply has been received by commission
                            from Holland to this request despite fact that commission was optimistic
                            about favorable reply. Please take matter up with Foreign Office
                            informally and cable your opinion as to why such reasonable request has
                            not received favorable consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>